BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Small Wonders
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T170000
UID:260324OYNy9MMO2EagEgWIHXL7lA
DESCRIPTION:Call for Art: Small Wonders\n\nSome of the most exquisite beau
 ty can be captured in the smallest of images and objects: the iridescence 
 of a hummingbird in flight\, a millefiori paperweight\, Faberge eggs\, or 
 a miniature woven basket. These pieces are modest in size but powerful in 
 creativity and expression.\n\nHealdsburg Center for the Arts \\(HCA\\) inv
 ites artists to submit paintings\, original fine art prints\, collage\, mi
 xed media\, drawings\, fiber arts\, sculptures\, ceramics\, and jewelry fo
 r this exhibition.\n\nApplication Requirements:\n\n- Platform: All applica
 tions must be submitted via EntryThingy\n\n- Eligibility: Work must be ori
 ginal and completed within the past two years. Photos in the application m
 ust represent the actual work intended for exhibition.\n\n- Size/Weight: A
 rtwork must not exceed 12" x 12" unframed \\(144 sq in\\) or 196 sq in fra
 med. Maximum weight is 40 lbs.\n\n- Display: 2-D pieces must be securely w
 ired \\(no alligator clips\\). 3-D work must be stable\; artists are respo
 nsible for on-site assembly if required.\n\n- Sales: All work must be for 
 sale. HCA retains a 40% commission\; artists receive 60%. Please list reta
 il prices only.\n\nKey Dates:\n\n- Entry Deadline: May 10\, 2026 \\(9 PM\\
 )\n\n- Notification of Selection: By May 13\, 2026\n\n- Shipped Work Deadl
 ine: Wednesday\, May 27\, 2026 \\(must include pre-paid return label\\)\n\
 n- Hand-Delivery: Sunday\, May 31 \\(12–4 PM\\) and Monday\, June 1 \\(1
 1 AM–1 PM\\)\n\n- Exhibition Dates: June 4\, 2026 – July 19\, 2026\n\n
 - Opening Reception: Saturday\, June 6\, 2026 \\(4–6 PM\\)\n\n- Pick-up/
 Return Shipping: July 19 \\(12–4 PM\\) and July 20 \\(11 AM–1 PM\\)\; 
 shipping the week of July 20.\n\nEntry Fees:\n\n- Non-Members: $50 \\(1 en
 try\\)\, $55 \\(2 entries\\)\, $60 \\(3 entries\\). Includes a $60 yearly 
 supporter membership.\n\n- Current Members: $40 \\(1 entry\\)\, $45 \\(2 e
 ntries\\)\, $50 \\(3 entries\\).
LOCATION:Healdsburg Center for the Arts
URL:https://healdsburgcenterforthearts.org/small-wonders-2/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bachata with ALEX
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T203000
UID:260319ngAHb5N8QEip4O9Ov-i54w
DESCRIPTION:Bachata with ALEX\n\nReady to take your bachata to the next le
 vel?\n\nThis intermediate bachata class is for dancers who have already ma
 stered the basics and are ready for a new challenge. We’ll build on your
  foundation with a focus on more intricate footwork\, technique\, and part
 ner work.\n\nAdvanced turn patterns and combinations\n\nStyling and body m
 ovement to add flair to your dancing\n\nMusicality to connect with the rhy
 thm and emotion of the music\n\nFeeling comfortable with your basic bachat
 a steps and ready for more?\n\nOur intermediate bachata class is designe
 d for dancers who want to elevate their skills. We’ll move beyond the fu
 ndamentals to focus on more complex technique\, footwork\, and partner wo
 rk.\n\nThis class will help you:\n\nRefine your leading and following\n\nL
 earn combinations and techniques\n\nDevelop your personal style and musica
 lity\n\nIf you’re ready to add some fire to your dancing\, this is the c
 lass for you!\n\nImportant Details\n\nBasic steps and turns required. We
 ’ll be moving into combinations\, so a solid grasp of your basic steps i
 s essential.\n\nNo partner necessary: Come solo or bring a friend—eithe
 r way\, you’ll have plenty of opportunities to dance.\n\nPlease wear non
 -marking shoe soles: This helps us keep our dance floor in great condition
 .\n\nCome join us and discover the joy of bachata! We can’t wait to see 
 you on the dance floor.
LOCATION:Salsa Dance Marin
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/bachata-with-alex/17285
 108/2026-03-31T19
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beginner Salsa - Tuesdays
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T183000
UID:260319n3XwaJK3NU6gR9JVlKA2pQ
DESCRIPTION:Ready to dance? Join our beginner salsa class where no experie
 nce or partner is needed. Just comfortable shoes and desire to have fun!\n
 \nGreat for first timers!\n\nNo dance experience required\n\nNon-marking s
 hoes soles\n\nNo partner necessary\n\nOur relaxed environment is perfect f
 or learning salsa basics\, as we make it fun and enjoyable. In this class 
 you will learn basic directional steps\, proper frame for partner-work and
  simple turn patterns. We organize our curriculum so that the movements ar
 e easy to remember. Join us to learn the fundamentals! No experience is ne
 cessary and no partner is required. Drop-in fee is $20.\n\nDate & Time: Tu
 esdays @ 5:30PM – 6:30PM\n\nAddress: 4140 Redwood Highway \\#8 San Rafae
 l\, CA\n\nNote: Arrive 10 minutes before. No floor marking shoe soles allo
 wed.
LOCATION:Salsa Dance Marin
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/beginner-salsa-tuesdays
 /17157360/2026-03-31T17
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Intermediate Salsa Class
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T193000
UID:260318Th6R2qWhIkOjQcz_ZXC6tA
DESCRIPTION:This class is designed for dancers who have a solid grasp of t
 he basics and are eager to expand their repertoire with more complex and f
 luid movements.\n\nPre- requisite:\n\nSalsa Class Beginners\n\nEach week\,
  we’ll break down a new move\, focusing on the technique and connection 
 that will make you a more confident and stylish dancer. We’ll go beyond 
 the foundational steps to cover a wide range of essential intermediate pat
 terns and styling\, including:\n\nTurns and Spins:\n\nMaster your inside a
 nd outside turns\, double spins\, and the elegant 360 and Hand Toss moves.
 \n\nIntricate Patterns:\n\nLearn to execute the 360\, wrap\, as well as va
 rious Cross Body Lead variations like the U-Turn and Spiral.\n\nFootwork a
 nd Styling:\n\nEnhance your rhythm and flair with advanced footwork like t
 he Suzy Q\, Front Tap\, and Mambo Step. We’ll also work on styling with 
 a wrap and improving your posture and upper body movement.\n\nThis class i
 s your chance to refine your technique\, improve your lead-follow connecti
 on\, and add a variety of fun and dynamic moves to your salsa vocabulary. 
 Join us and elevate your dance!\n\nDetails:\n\nNo partner necessary — ro
 tations ensure everyone gets to dance.\n\nPlease wear non-marking shoe so
 les to protect the floor.\n\nArrive 10 minutes early to warm up and get s
 ettled.\n\nDate & Time: Tuesdays @ 6:30PM – 7:30PM
LOCATION:Salsa Dance Marin
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/intermediate-salsa-clas
 s/17159571/2026-03-31T18
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T180000
UID:260318PR9eJpcE1k6frz_SKs-W-w
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\nAPRIL EXHIBIT: THE PO
 ETIC LANDSCAPE\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\nRECEP
 TION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILLER and
  PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by feature
 d guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.  Be 
 sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beautiful 
 work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.\n\nSonoma County 
 artist\, Karen Miller\, presents The Poetic Landscape\, pastel paintings t
 hat convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting with the intrinsic
  beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid shapes and rhyt
 hmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true poetic interlud
 e.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,” turning to the 
 sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the river’s edge\
 , concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing in “Fetch.”
   The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a shaded secret sp
 ot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\, these works tru
 ly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Miller remarked “ 
 As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surrounding us\, I try to 
 express my painterly response in hopes it will engender recognition by the
  viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting the Gallery on M
 arch 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stairway Smallworks 
 Showcase features Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\, a collection of waterco
 lors that create an atmosphere that is both introspective and magical.  F
 amiliar domestic scenes are transformed as humans interact with animals an
 d birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” the red-headed young
  woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahead\, flanked by her 
 avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like taking a mini-step o
 n the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nMeet the artist: Rapp
  will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 from 11am to 6 pm.\n
 \nAlso join us for ART NITE HEALDSBURG\, Thursday\, April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.
   The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets to Art.  ART NITE Hea
 ldsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is a community event cele
 brating art and creativity with over 20 galleries participating.  ArtNite
 Healdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Center Street\, Healdsburg\,
  CA 95448. \\(707\\) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 pm.    www.upsta
 irsart gallery.net \n\nFor further information: Contact: Beverly Bird\, Pr
 ess Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T180000
UID:2603144PH8VYOvN0KIl-q6kK57lQ
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\n**APRIL EXHIBIT: THE 
 POETIC LANDSCAPE**\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\n*
 *RECEPTION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILL
 ER and PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by f
 eatured guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.
   Be sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beau
 tiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.**\n\nSonoma
  County artist\, **Karen Miller\,** presents **The Poetic Landscape\,** pa
 stel paintings that convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting wi
 th the intrinsic beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid
  shapes and rhythmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true
  poetic interlude.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,”
  turning to the sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the
  river’s edge\, concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing
  in “Fetch.”  The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a 
 shaded secret spot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\,
  these works truly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Mill
 er remarked “ As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surroundin
 g us\, I try to express my painterly response in hopes it will engender re
 cognition by the viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting 
 the Gallery on March 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stai
 rway Smallworks Showcase features **Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\,** a c
 ollection of watercolors that create an atmosphere that is both introspect
 ive and magical.  Familiar domestic scenes are transformed as humans inte
 ract with animals and birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” 
 the red-headed young woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahe
 ad\, flanked by her avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like 
 taking a mini-step on the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nM
 eet the artist: Rapp will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 
 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nAlso join us for **ART NITE HEALDSBURG**\, Thursday\
 , April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.  The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets
  to Art.  ART NITE Healdsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is
  a community event celebrating art and creativity with over 20 galleries p
 articipating.  ArtNiteHealdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Cente
 r Street\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. (707) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 
 pm.    **www.upstairsart gallery.net** \n\nFor further information: Con
 tact: Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Museum Member SWAP Week
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T100000
UID:260313nAha28p68E6lgqnDvw0arw
DESCRIPTION:Discover the many incredible museums in Sonoma County by spend
 ing a week museum-hopping! Current members at ANY of the 10 participating 
 museums will receive reciprocal **FREE** entry (up to 4 guests) for the 
 entire week! *Please check each museum’s website (below) for hours and 
 restrictions in advance.*\n\n**Participating Museums:**\n\n**California In
 dian Museum & Cultural Center**\n\n**Charles M. Schulz Museum**\n\n**Child
 ren’s Museum of Sonoma County**\\*\n\n**Luther Burbank Home & Garden**\n
 \n**Museum of Sonoma County**\n\n**Pacific Coast Air Museum**\n\n**Petalum
 a Art Center**\n\n**Sebastopol Center for the Arts**\n\n**Sonoma Botanical
  Garden**\n\n**Sonoma Valley Museum of Art**\n\n\\**Must visit with a chil
 d to receive entry to the Children’s Museum of Sonoma County.*\n\n**Not 
 a member? Join any of the participating museums to enjoy the weeklong rec
 iprocal benefit!** The Schulz Museum will offer door prizes for new Member
 s who sign up in person at the Museum on the SWAP Week kick-off date\, Sat
 urday\, March 28 (**memberships** start at $50 and include special events
 \, discounts\, exclusive collectibles\, and more). For more information\, 
 call (707) 284-1273.
LOCATION:Charles M. Schulz Museum
URL:https://schulzmuseum.org/member-swap-week-2026/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bottle Baby Breakfast Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T160000
UID:2603125gxwLFa1-EiAAaizNxN7Bg
DESCRIPTION:Tiny Hooves\, Big Hearts: Our Ongoing Rescue Mission\n\nAt Goa
 tlandia\, our mission is simple: to give love\, safety\, and a second chan
 ce to animals who need it most.\n\nWe were recently called to rescue three
  baby goats. These tiny babies are now safe at Goatlandia\, and they need 
 bottle feeding several times a day to stay healthy and thrive.\n\nThat’s
  Where You Come In: The Bottle Baby Breakfast Club\n\nStarting March 6th\,
  join us for a heartwarming hour on the farm\, bottle-feeding and cuddling
  our newest rescues while supporting their care.\n\nYour $250 donation \\(
 covers milk and supplies for weeks of feedings\\) includes admission for u
 p to four guests for a private\, unforgettable visit to Goatlandia.\n\nCom
 e share the love\, feel the magic\, and help us give these little ones the
  future they deserve.
LOCATION:Goatlandia
URL:https://www.goatlandia.org/bottle-babies-breakfast-club
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sonoma County Volunteer Fair
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T190000
UID:260308lJnP30il4UqsOyDEATEJEg
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate community and get connected at the Sonoma County Vol
 unteer Fair.\n\nThis free community event brings together dozens of local 
 nonprofits\, public agencies\, and community groups looking for volunteers
 \, board members\, and supporters. Whether you're looking for a one-time o
 pportunity or a long-term way to give back\, the Volunteer Fair makes it e
 asy to find a cause that aligns with your interests and skills.\n\nIn hono
 r of César Chávez Day and National Volunteer Month\, attendees can also 
 participate in an on-site service project supporting The Botanical Bus\, a
  bilingual mobile clinic providing culturally centered healthcare for Lati
 ne and Indigenous immigrant communities.\n\nStop by anytime during the eve
 nt to:\n\n~Meet local nonprofits and community organizations\n\n~Learn abo
 ut volunteer opportunities across Sonoma County\n\n~Participate in assembl
 ing care bags for the Botanical Bus mobile clinic\n\n~Contribute to a comm
 unity art project honoring César Chávez Day\n\n~Connect with neighbors w
 ho care about strengthening our community\n\nEveryone is welcome — indiv
 iduals\, families\, students\, and anyone interested in making a differenc
 e.
LOCATION:The Backdrop
URL:https://cvnl.org/sonoma-county-volunteer-fair/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:March Month of Flowers Challenge
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T120000
UID:260306dhIfNcvEJ0KjuRNzhcq7sw
DESCRIPTION:**Starting March 1st begins the "March Month of Flowers Challe
 nge" (online).** \n\nYou'll receive a list of prompts for every day in Mar
 ch. \n\nCreate an art piece related to the prompt.\n\nShare in our privat
 e Facebook group.\n\nBe inspired and give inspiration to others.\n\n**Only
  $5**\, so everyone can join and share in this creative adventure!\n\n***M
 arch Month of Flowers* Challenge** is here to give you a creative outlet
 \, some structure\, and respite from your brain. \n\nWhen you pick up a b
 rush\, pen\, or pencil (thread\, clay\, fabric…)\, your brain gets a res
 t and becomes more alive and flexible. The world around you becomes more 
 alive\; you pick up on shades\, details\, and patterns all around you. Y
 our intuition gets stronger. And fear lessens\, anxiety fades\, and curios
 ity grows. You stop worrying about making mistakes\, and instead\, you fi
 nd the freedom to simply create
URL:https://www.taradickinson.com/project-page/workshops
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beginning Improv Class
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T203000
UID:260304SNjRc2oE1US_aw81Tcdr6g
DESCRIPTION:Welcome to 6-week introduction to the world of improv. It's su
 per fun\, playful and supportive!\n\nWe'll focus on games and exercises de
 signed to get us out of our judging minds and into a playful state of flow
 \, and start exploring scene work while learning the basic elements that m
 ake improv work. You'll learn to think on your feet (which actually means 
 to STOP thinking)\, trust your instincts\, and work collaboratively with o
 thers. Expect lots of laughter\, spontaneity\, and unforgettable moments.\
 n\nYou don't consider yourself “naturally” quick\, funny or outgoing? 
 Perfect! You don't need to be to do improv\, all you need to do is show up
 --truly! You will surprise yourself\, then watch your confidence grow. Imp
 rov tools can help us be more comfortable with ourselves\, thus enabling u
 s to be more relaxed and engaged in our work\, social situations or onstag
 e\, for those who perform or wish to.\n\nMostly it’s just really\, reall
 y fun!
LOCATION:Redwood Empire Ice Arena (Studio)
URL:https://www.ziplineimprov.com/current-classes
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Family Stick Loom Weaving
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T173000
UID:260228xpV37c0x_EmoCHWicYkyGw
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSaturday\, March 21\, 2026 2:00 – 3:30 PM\n\nLoc
 ation\n\nRoom 110\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nFamily\, Kids\n\nAg
 e\\(s\\)\n\n7-12\n\nAll children must be accompanied by an adult to attend
 .\n\n$30 – Per Family\, max of 3 people. Learn ancient stick loom weavin
 g in this hands-on class. Create a beautiful tapestry using natural materi
 als\, simple techniques\, and your choice of colors.\n\nAbout the Class\n\
 nCome learn the ancient craft of weaving with a stick loom! In this family
 -friendly class\, you’ll learn to hand-weave a simple tapestry using sti
 cks as your loom. The demonstration will include setting up the warp threa
 ds\, learning a simple over-under stitch pattern and the final knot step. 
 There will be a variety of stick shapes to choose from and plenty of room 
 to play with pattern and color. And voila! You’ll leave the class with y
 our stick-loom tapestry \\(either in progress or completed\, depending on 
 the chosen scale\\). Hang your weaving on your wall to bring nature indoor
 s or from a tree to bring your artistry outside! This class is open to par
 ents with their children ages 7 through 12.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/family-stick-loom-weaving/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"You're My Neighbor" Art Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T180000
UID:260227mb4UCiUWkkiHdPhJIcE6ug
DESCRIPTION:Come out to Point Reyes and celebrate neighbors!   \n\nFrom 
 mooing cows and soaring birds to friendly faces down the road\, Cedars art
 ists take a joyful look at their Marin County neighborhood. This exhibitio
 n explores all the things that make their corner of the world special—op
 en fields\, wild creatures\, familiar people\, and the everyday moments in
  between. Through colorful\, thoughtful\, and imaginative works\, “You
 ’re My Neighbor” celebrates the beauty of living side by side and shar
 ing a place we call home.\n\n​Cedars “You’re My Neighbor!” art exh
 ibition runs from March 3 through April 12\, 2026
LOCATION:Toby's Feed Barn
URL:https://www.cedarslife.org/events
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Introduction to Printmaking Spring Session
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T193000
UID:260216F2nrIfgpJ0aeUNEIilwHog
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nTuesdays\, March 31 – April 28\, 2026 5:30 Pm 
 – 7:30 PM\n\nExperience Level\n\nBeginning\n\nPrintmaking\n\nAge\\(s\\)\
 n\n16\\+\n\n$195 – Registration Cost $30 – Materials Fee $225 – Tota
 l Registration CostWhat exactly is printmaking? We invite you into our pri
 nt studio to experience a beginner’s journey through this incredible art
  form\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nWhat is printmaking? We invite you into our p
 rint studio to experience a fun beginner’s journey through this incredib
 le art form in five paced weeks. Join Kelly in this unique introduction to
  print through the world of monotype\, relief\, intaglio and stencil scree
 nprinting. This popular multi-session workshop is only taught twice per ye
 ar in the spring and fall seasons. Students will try various techniques in
  this guided\, hands-on class to create a beginning portfolio of prints. L
 earn a basic understanding of the four classic methods within the family o
 f printmaking and gain access to our member’s print studio to continue w
 orking on your own projects. This class is perfect for absolute beginners 
 or even experienced artists who may need a refresher course in printmaking
 . \n\nMonotype – Create a single print on a flat matrix using ink and a
  variety of marks and  textures\n\nRelief – Carve\, ink and block print
  using a mini speedy carve block and a linocut tool\n\nIntaglio – Draw\,
  scratch and ink onto a surface to roll out a creative print using a small
  press\n\nStencil – Pull a silkscreen and learn to transfer a flat stenc
 il to make a colorful printed impression\n\nNo prior printmaking experienc
 e is necessary. This class requires hand dexterity to maneuver carving too
 ls and studio equipment. Students must feel comfortable handling machinery
 .\n\nMembership has its benefits\n\nAll Silver Memberships and above recei
 ve 10% off the registration cost for any class purchase over $40. Material
 s fees are not discounted.\n\nBecome a member today and find community\, c
 onnection\, and creativity.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/introduction-to-printmaking
 -spring-session/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
