BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Good Friday Taize Meditation and Chant Service
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T170000
UID:260330UMdyev52k0ivkKjIJWiG8Q
DESCRIPTION:The Sebastopol Methodist Church will have a special service to
  mark Good Friday\, April 3\, from 4 to 5 p.m.\, with an ecumenical servic
 e of song\, chant\, scripture and meditation originating from the Taize mo
 nastic community of Taize\, France. Founded in 1940\, by a Swiss individua
 l Fr. Roger Schutz who became a monastic\, Taize worship is a meditative\,
  ecumenical form of Christian prayer characterized by simple\, repetitive 
 songs and chants\, Scripture readings\, periods of profound silence\, and 
 candlelight. Led by pianist and cantor Andy Darrow\, the service focuses o
 n peace\, contemplation\, and reconciliation. The spirit of Taize is to fo
 ster peace among all people. The simple service consists of song\, using t
 he simple chants of the Taize community\, scripture\, extended periods of 
 silence\, and prayers for the world. Taize prayer is widely practiced in s
 tudent religious centers and retreat houses\, and draws 100\,000 visitors 
 annually to its center in France.
LOCATION:Sebastopol Methodist Church
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/good-friday-taize-medit
 ation-and-chant-service/18463269/2026-04-03T16
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
