BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wreckless Strangers Live at Papermill Creek Saloon
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T203000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T203000
UID:2603198v2ZahapyEKE3kjSmg8Qrw
DESCRIPTION:Thrilled that their newly released singles are getting nationa
 l radio airplay and moving up the Top 100 Americana Singles and Top 100 AA
 A Singles Charts\,Wreckless Strangers continue their album release celebr
 ation with several shows in the San Francisco Bay Area\, including Lucca 
 Bar & Grill in Benicia\, the newly reopened historic Papermill Creek Salo
 on in West Marin\, a stint at the Golden Gate Park Bandshell\, a fundrais
 er for Challenged Athletes Foundation\, and more.\n\nWreckless Strangers 
 return to their roots with their forthcoming studio album\,Dirty Souls. Th
 e six-song collection marks the band’s rawest and most visceral effort t
 o date — a modern take on the arena rock of the ’70s and ’80s that i
 nspired their earliest musical influences. The first single\, "Dirty Soul
 \," came out on January 23 and is getting radio play across the nation\, a
 nd is available on most streaming platforms. Their second single\, “The
  Runaround\,” was released on February 27\, and the full album comes 
 out on March 27. Concert attendees will have the opportunity to purchase c
 opies of the CD at the live shows. \n\nDirty Souls is the band’s third
  studio outing under the tutelage of Grammy-winning producer Dave Way\, w
 ho fosters a level of depth and organic cohesion that firmly establishes W
 reckless Strangers in San Francisco’s storied rock ’n’ roll legacy. 
 The songwriting is among their most intimate and personal\, exploring them
 es of relationships\, loss\, empowerment\, and perseverance. Co-lead singe
 rs Amber Morris and David Noble function as a single organism\, bringin
 g the songs to life with bluesy grit\, soul\, and humanity bolstered by ro
 ck-solid\, road-hewn grooves.\n\nVisit WrecklessStrangers.com and follow
  the band on social media for updates.\n\nWreckless Strangers is a collect
 ive of friends and musicians carrying the torch for San Francisco’s gran
 d rock ‘n’ roll tradition. Their unique blend of “Ameri-Cali Soul”
  melds the contemporary blues stylings of Bonnie Raitt and Boz Scaggs\; th
 e songwriting sensibilities of Sons of Champlin and Fleetwood Mac\; the sw
 ashbuckling Americana of the Lost Planet Airmen and Peter Rowan\; and the 
 funk of Sly Stone and Tower of Power with a dash of Grateful Dead and Jeff
 erson Airplane for flavor and unpredictability. With soaring vocal harmoni
 es and burning instrumental improvisation\, framed by concise\, poignant o
 riginal songwriting\, Wreckless Strangers seek to honor and carry forth th
 e brand of free-spirited musical fun and adventure that defines the Bay Ar
 ea. \n\nThe band features Amber Morris on lead vocals\; David Noble on
  lead guitar and lead vocals\; Joshua Zucker on bass and vocals\; Mick H
 ellman on drums and vocals\; Rob Anderson on guitar and vocals\; and Fl
 etcher Nielsen on keys. \n\nThe band was recently invited back to perform
  live on Nashville’s famed Americana Roots radio station\, WMOT\, and pe
 rformed at NAMM in Southern California in January.
LOCATION:Papermill Creek Saloon
URL:https://papermillcreeksaloon.com/events/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T180000
UID:260318A3MYtnJADE--1lSGu5p98w
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\nAPRIL EXHIBIT: THE PO
 ETIC LANDSCAPE\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\nRECEP
 TION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILLER and
  PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by feature
 d guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.  Be 
 sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beautiful 
 work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.\n\nSonoma County 
 artist\, Karen Miller\, presents The Poetic Landscape\, pastel paintings t
 hat convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting with the intrinsic
  beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid shapes and rhyt
 hmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true poetic interlud
 e.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,” turning to the 
 sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the river’s edge\
 , concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing in “Fetch.”
   The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a shaded secret sp
 ot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\, these works tru
 ly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Miller remarked “ 
 As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surrounding us\, I try to 
 express my painterly response in hopes it will engender recognition by the
  viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting the Gallery on M
 arch 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stairway Smallworks 
 Showcase features Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\, a collection of waterco
 lors that create an atmosphere that is both introspective and magical.  F
 amiliar domestic scenes are transformed as humans interact with animals an
 d birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” the red-headed young
  woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahead\, flanked by her 
 avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like taking a mini-step o
 n the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nMeet the artist: Rapp
  will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 from 11am to 6 pm.\n
 \nAlso join us for ART NITE HEALDSBURG\, Thursday\, April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.
   The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets to Art.  ART NITE Hea
 ldsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is a community event cele
 brating art and creativity with over 20 galleries participating.  ArtNite
 Healdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Center Street\, Healdsburg\,
  CA 95448. \\(707\\) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 pm.    www.upsta
 irsart gallery.net \n\nFor further information: Contact: Beverly Bird\, Pr
 ess Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Faye Dorman is the Featured Artist for April at Sky Ranch Gallery
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T150000
UID:260317PxfyLVpnF0G37aF6RADpxA
DESCRIPTION:My oil paintings explore the emotional\, human landscape.\n\nT
 he malleability of oil paint allows her to layer color\, to scrape away an
 d rebuild and to let brushwork remain as a record of the hand and feeling 
 behind it. \n\n   My years of being a therapist and sitting with faces 
 that hold and reflect emotion is what I hope to capture in a portrait. I 
 invite viewers to recognize their own internal world reflected back.
LOCATION:Sky Ranch Gallery
URL:https://www.skyranchgallery.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T180000
UID:260314Cjsx8IV79EGOi8RMGnGFRA
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\n**APRIL EXHIBIT: THE 
 POETIC LANDSCAPE**\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\n*
 *RECEPTION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILL
 ER and PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by f
 eatured guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.
   Be sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beau
 tiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.**\n\nSonoma
  County artist\, **Karen Miller\,** presents **The Poetic Landscape\,** pa
 stel paintings that convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting wi
 th the intrinsic beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid
  shapes and rhythmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true
  poetic interlude.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,”
  turning to the sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the
  river’s edge\, concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing
  in “Fetch.”  The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a 
 shaded secret spot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\,
  these works truly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Mill
 er remarked “ As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surroundin
 g us\, I try to express my painterly response in hopes it will engender re
 cognition by the viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting 
 the Gallery on March 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stai
 rway Smallworks Showcase features **Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\,** a c
 ollection of watercolors that create an atmosphere that is both introspect
 ive and magical.  Familiar domestic scenes are transformed as humans inte
 ract with animals and birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” 
 the red-headed young woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahe
 ad\, flanked by her avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like 
 taking a mini-step on the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nM
 eet the artist: Rapp will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 
 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nAlso join us for **ART NITE HEALDSBURG**\, Thursday\
 , April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.  The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets
  to Art.  ART NITE Healdsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is
  a community event celebrating art and creativity with over 20 galleries p
 articipating.  ArtNiteHealdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Cente
 r Street\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. (707) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 
 pm.    **www.upstairsart gallery.net** \n\nFor further information: Con
 tact: Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
