BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Monica Da Silva & Complicated Animals
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T000000
UID:260327ju55P56zWUCpJJ4_PZz6Sg
DESCRIPTION:Monica da Silva grew up living between The United States and B
 elém\, Brazil\, a city on the Amazon River. A love of travel and foreign 
 language helped to forge her unique sound. \n\n \n\nParalleling her life\,
  da Silva's music contains an eclectic mix of Brazilian and American influ
 ences. Her sound can be classified as International Fusion\, as it is heav
 ily influenced by Brazilian music\, namely Bossa Nova\, but also incorpora
 tes elements of Lounge\, Electronica\, Indie Pop\, and Worldbeat. Da Silva
  brings her cultural diversity to her songs\, smoothly flowing between Eng
 lish\, Portuguese\, and Spanish.\n\n \n\nIn 2010\, da Silva released her a
 lbum "Brasilissima" . The record featured songs in both of her native lang
 uages - English and Portuguese. The first single "Aí Então"\, “was cho
 sen by Putumayo World Music to be included on their compilation “Brazili
 an Beat”. The upbeat\, psychedelic track "That's Not The Way" was chosen
  by the music director of ESPN to be played during the programming of The 
 FIFA World Cup in 2014\, alongside major recording artists Coldplay\, Sér
 gio Mendes\, Pitbull\, Jennifer Lopez\, The Black Eyed Peas\, Stan Getz\, 
 and Astrud Gilberto. \n\nDa Silva's single "Soldado de Amor" \\(2017\\) ha
 s been featured in the BBC One series "The Replacement”\, in the Paramou
 nt Network series "American Woman"\, and in a 2019 campaign for the design
 er Tory Burch.\n\nHer music has also been featured in the series "Heartlan
 d"\, and in an ad for Patron Tequila. She is currently recording a new\, f
 ull-length solo album\, as well as writing and recording with her project\
 , Complicated Animals.
LOCATION:JaM Cellars
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107954583?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mitch Woods
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T203000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T000000
UID:260327RIby8zj9g0SOVGwbc4_-og
DESCRIPTION:http://mitchwoods.com/about-2/about/\n\nMitch Woods is a seaso
 ned blues and boogie-woogie pianist whose dynamic sound has earned him a p
 lace in the hearts of music lovers worldwide. For over three decades\, Woo
 ds and his band\, The Rocket 88s\, have been torchbearers of a great Ameri
 can musical tradition\, mixing early jump blues\, rhythm & blues\, and New
  Orleans-inspired rhythms into their unique rock-a-boogie style. Drawing i
 nfluence from legends like Louis Jordan\, Professor Longhair\, and Fats Do
 mino\, Woods blends raw energy with sophisticated piano playing\, creating
  a sound that feels timeless yet fresh.
LOCATION:Sonoma Speakeasy and American Music Hall
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/108106383?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
