BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Marty O'Reilly & The Old Soul Orchestra
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T203000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T000000
UID:2603275oW_m9s090OMja3SSE_t7g
DESCRIPTION:There’s something about Marty O’Reilly’s music that feel
 s like it’s always been here—like an old story being told in a new way
 . His voice is raw and real\, his guitar playing gritty and soulful. It’
 s music that doesn’t try to be anything other than honest\, and that’s
  exactly why it hits so hard.\n\nHe pulls inspiration from the roots of Am
 ericana\; his sound references folk greats like Woody Guthrie\, blues lege
 nds like Howlin’ Wolf\,  gospel pioneers like Sister Rosetta Thorpe\, an
 d master storytellers like Tom Waits. It’s a sound that captivates and c
 onnects audiences\, and leaves them wanting more.\n\nHis live shows aren
 ’t just concerts—they’re cathartic experiences. One moment it’s so
 ft and haunting\, the next it’s wild and electric. The kind that stay wi
 th you long after the lights come up.\n\nBut it’s not just about the sou
 nd. Marty’s songs dig deep into the human experience—loneliness\, conn
 ection\, love\, loss. Whether it’s an intimate solo set or a full band s
 how\, he makes every audience feel like they’re part of the story.\n\nOv
 er the years\, Marty has built a dedicated following through relentless to
 uring and staying true to his craft. He’s shared the stage with artists 
 like Shakey Graves\, St. Paul & The Broken Bones\, Sarah Jarosz\, and Alic
 e O’Donovan and played at festivals like Bottlerock\, SXSW\, and High Si
 erra Music Festival\, but his focus has always been on making music that m
 eans something.\n\nMarty has poured everything into his music—spending y
 ears on the road\, self-funding his albums\, and navigating the ups and do
 wns of life as an independent artist\, husband\, and father. But through i
 t all\, he’s never lost sight of why he started: to make honest music th
 at connects.\n\nIf you’re looking for music that feels real\, that makes
  you stop and listen\, Marty O’Reilly is someone you need to hear.
LOCATION:Mystic Theatre & Music Hall
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/108060942?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Opening Reception for Quiet Structure by Roberta Ahrens
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T200000
UID:260326ihsnwOmO5UGxghGu3sWWOw
DESCRIPTION:What: Quiet Structure \\+ Opening Reception\n\nWhen: Opening R
 eception - Saturday\, April 4th\, 2025\, 5 - 8 pm\, Show Run - March 24th 
 - April 26th\n\nLocation: Usher Gallery\, 1 Petaluma Blvd North\, Petaluma
 \n\n"Quiet Structure" showcases a selection of contemporary botanical and 
 water-based works by Roberta Ahrens.\n\nRoberta Ahrens is a California-bas
 ed artist whose practice centers on contemporary works created on handmade
  cracked linen. This featured exhibition will be on view at Usher Gallery 
 from March 24th to April 26th. \n\nJoin us for the opening reception to e
 njoy live music by Sophia Rayne\, refreshments\, and an opportunity to mee
 t and connect with the artist. \n\nArtist Statement:\n\n"I create contemp
 orary botanical and water-based works on my own handmade cracked linen. Th
 e surface is my primary collaborator built\, fractured\, carved\, and laye
 red with acrylic\, watercolor\, and clay base until it holds both structur
 e and light. I’m drawn to what I think of as nature’s architecture: th
 e way a petal opens like a vault\, the way water forms strata through move
 ment and pressure. Rather than simply depicting flowers or waves\, I inter
 pret them in a wider artistic landscape. Scale matters. Many pieces are me
 ant to be experienced bodily\, and emotionally\, ways that reveal subtle s
 hifts in depth and translucency as light moves across them. With both bota
 nicals and water\, I pursue a shared language of balance and motion where 
 stillness and force exist at the same time. My intention is to offer a pla
 ce to slow down and feel the quiet intelligence of the natural world."\n\n
 - Roberta Ahrens\n\nMore details about Roberta Ahrens and her work can be 
 found at: https://www.robertaahrens.com/
LOCATION:Usher Gallery
URL:https://ushergallerypetaluma.com/blogs/exhibitions
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:KPFZ - The Tempest - Celtic Rock Band
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T220000
