UID:260324suFMl8Ga-0-k36hozmrQng
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSaturday\, April 4\, 2026 2:00 PM – 4:30 PM\n\nL
 ocation\n\nRoom 201\, Fiber Arts Studio\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\
 n\nEvent Categories: Fiber Arts\, Sustainability\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n16\\+\n\
 nRegistration Cost:\n\n$40\n\nMaterials Fee:\n\nBring Your Own Trash!\n\nT
 otal Registration Cost:\n\n$40\n\nUpcycle trash into fabulous wearable art
 ! Create a DIY eco-cuff bracelet from toilet paper rolls. Materials provid
 ed or BYOT. Join our trashion class.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nJust in time fo
 r Trashion season and beyond. Learn how to turn common household trash int
 o a fabulous\, wearable work of art. You’ll create your own eco-cuff bra
 celet\, starting with an empty toilet paper roll and adding your own creat
 ive flair. All materials are provided\, but you are welcome to BYOT: bring
  your own trash! Beginners to advanced makers are welcome. A fun\, inspiri
 ng time is guaranteed! “Back in 2023\, trashion queen and ‘Advanced St
 yle’ icon Debra Rapoport came from New York to judge Sonoma Community Ce
 nter’s annual Trashion Fashion Runway Show\, and to teach a workshop on 
 how to make eco-cuff art bracelets. In this class\, I’ll show you how I 
 use her toilet paper roll technique to create my own hand-painted\, mixed-
 media wearable art pieces\, and I’ll guide you in making your own unique
  eco-cuff bracelet from reclaimed\, recycled\, and repurposed materials.
 ”
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/eco-cuff-bracelets/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
