BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Monet and Venice Lecture
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T173000
UID:260325yUrACHhXE0qqsZ8KmoXRuw
DESCRIPTION:Please join SRJC Art History Professor Heidi Saleh for an upco
 ming lecture examining Claude Monet's celebrated 1908 Venetian campaign.\n
 \nDesigned as a companion to the Monet and Venice exhibition currently on 
 view \\(3/21/26 &ndash\; 7/26/26\\) at the de Young Museum in San Francisc
 o\, this talk will explore the historical and stylistic context of Monet's
  time in the Floating City. We will analyze his approach to seriality\, hi
 s technique for capturing light on water\, and how these canvases fit into
  the broader trajectory of late Impressionism. \n\nWhether you have alread
 y visited the de Young exhibition or are planning a trip\, this lecture wi
 ll provide a deeper framework for appreciating and engaging with these wor
 ks.
LOCATION:Petaluma Arts Center
URL:https://mynorthbaytickets.ticketsauce.com/e/monet-and-venice?aff=citys
 park
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
