BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Overeaters Anonymous (OA) Newcomer Meeting in Santa Rosa
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260405T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260405T170000
UID:260212IDSWbZRPF06cZVWOsSsp4Q
DESCRIPTION:Is Food a Problem for You? You Are Not Alone.\n\nOvereaters An
 onymous \\(OA\\) is a fellowship of people who support each other in recov
 ering from compulsive eating and food behaviors. If you feel you have a pr
 oblem with food\, OA welcomes you—no matter what your background\, belie
 fs\, or eating habits.\n\nWe hold an in-person newcomer meeting on Sundays
  from 4:00 – 5:00 PM at Christ Church United Methodist\, 1717 Yulupa Ave
 .\, Room \\#4\, Santa Rosa. Contact: Abigail \\(707\\) 293-5888. You may v
 iew all North Bay OA in-person and online meetings at https://www.northbay
 oa.org/meetings.html .\n\nIn OA\, members experience spiritual\, emotional
 \, and physical recovery by practicing the Twelve Steps and living by thei
 r spiritual principles—one day at a time.\n\nOA is not a diet club or ca
 lorie-counting program.\n\nMembers have different plans of eating.\n\nOA d
 oes not endorse any specific food plan.\n\nIf food is causing problems in 
 your life\, you don’t have to struggle alone. Recovery is possible\, and
  help is available.\n\nVisit: https://www.northbayoa.org/\n\nFind a meetin
 g: https://www.northbayoa.org/meetings.html
LOCATION:Christ Church United Methodist
URL:https://www.northbayoa.org/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
