BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Developing Your Drawing Eye
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260406T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260406T130000
UID:260207NLJDksspOEeR1dTAmT_T-A
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nMondays\, March 9 – April 20\, 2026 10:00 AM –
  1:00 PM Exceptions: No class March 23\n\nExperience Level\n\nBeginning\n\
 nDrawing & Painting\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and older\n\n$270 – Registration
  Cost $10 – Materials Fee $280 – Total Registration CostDeveloping You
 r Drawing Eye\n\nLearn to draw without pressure or grades. Build foundatio
 nal skills at your own pace through observational techniques. Perfect for 
 beginners. Materials included.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nIt’s never too lat
 e to learn to draw – especially when nobody’s grading you. Whether you
  are an abject beginner\, haven’t picked up a pencil since high school\,
  or you’re a creative who has always felt intimidated by observational d
 rawing\, this six-week class is offered with you in mind. We’ll take the
  mystery – and the pressure – out of drawing from observation. You’l
 l learn how to really see like an artist\, practice simple techniques step
  by step\, and build skills at your own pace. No talent required\, and per
 fection is off the table. Studying observational drawing offers a foundati
 onal skill set that you will carry into every medium you might wish to exp
 lore. Discover the joy of drawing and build practical skills to expand you
 r creative expression! All materials are provided.\n\nMembership has its b
 enefits\n\nAll Silver Memberships and above receive 10% off the registrati
 on cost for any class purchase over $40. Materials fees are not discounted
 .\n\nBecome a member today and find community\, connection\, and creativit
 y.\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 116
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
