BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Brandlin Estate Wine & Food Tasting Experience
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T160000
UID:260312O37qgkuiAkylZUWhzUP8NA
DESCRIPTION:Born on the rugged slopes of Mount Veeder\, Brandlin Estate pr
 oduces wines of structure\, intensity\, and place. The Brandlin Experience
  offers an in-depth exploration of this historic vineyard site through a c
 urated tasting of five estate-grown wines—including Zinfandel from centu
 ry-old vines and the estate’s signature Cabernet Sauvignon. This seated\
 , guided experience invites guests to delve into the mountain terroir thro
 ugh the lens of small-lot winemaking. Each wine reflects the elevation\, e
 xposure\, and rocky soils that define the Brandlin Estate. For an added di
 mension\, guests may opt to include seasonal bites\, thoughtfully paired t
 o complement the structure and complexity of the wines. This experience is
  hosted at the picturesque Boathouse.
LOCATION:Cuvaison Tasting Salon (Indoors Only)
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/the-brandlin-estate-win
 e-food-tasting-experience/18318441/2026-04-09T11
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Greg Lamboy Music
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T000000
UID:260306jiHWxNvyGEG1zNuHcfIjWA
DESCRIPTION:Greg Lamboy is a Northern California singer-songwriter whose p
 erformances combine lyrical honesty\, melodic craft\, and soulful acoustic
  guitar. Known for his confident yet comforting stage presence\, Greg weav
 es together original songs and reimagined favorites that invite listeners 
 to slow down and connect. His music blends strength and sensitivity\, reve
 aling deep emotion without pretense and reminding audiences why live music
  matters. Greg has released five albums and continues to captivate audienc
 es across the region\, both as a solo artist and as frontman for the Ameri
 cana band Pacific Standard.
LOCATION:Finnegan's Marin Restaurant & Bar
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107759619?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Greg Lamboy - Live Every 2nd
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T210000
UID:260225YYOTrqJmBkiVktagGntzgA
DESCRIPTION:Greg Lamboy has called Finnegan's Marin home for over a decade
 . Every second Thursday of the month\, this Tiburon-based troubadour settl
 es into the warmly lit corner of Novato's beloved neighborhood pub and doe
 s what he does best: connects. An accomplished guitarist and award-winning
  songwriter\, Lamboy has earned his stripes across the Bay Area scene both
  as a solo artist and as frontman of Pacific Standard\, his soulful Americ
 ana band. His five acclaimed albums draw praise for melodies that are pitc
 h-perfect and lyrics that feel like they were written specifically for you
 . At Finnegan's\, a lively Irish pub and American bar and grill along a tr
 ee-lined street in downtown Novato\, Lamboy's intimate style is perfectly 
 at home. No pretense. No distance. Just a strong clear voice\, commanding 
 guitar\, and songs that\, as one critic put it\, lift you above the everyd
 ay. Come early\, grab a pint\, and let the music find you. https://greglam
 boy.com/\n\nEvery second Thursday of the month | Finnegan's Marin\, 877 Gr
 ant Ave\, Novato | Free
LOCATION:Finnegan's Marin
URL:https://www.finnegansmarin.com/events-calendar/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
