BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Making Citrus Curd with Merrilee Olson at Gold Ridge Organic Farms
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T130000
UID:260313p2aifZu8lU-fv5sWwsET-g
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a hands-on citrus curd making class led by chef an
 d food preservationist Merrilee Olson. Over three hours\, Merrilee will gu
 ide you through every step of making silky\, vibrant citrus curd — shari
 ng her expert techniques and secrets for achieving that perfect balance of
  tart\, sweet\, and luscious — using organic Meyer Lemons and Satsuma Ma
 ndarins grown right here on our 88-acre farm.\n\nThe experience begins wit
 h a ride aboard our apple-themed trolley out to the Apple Cottage\, where 
 the class takes place surrounded by the beauty of the farm. Each guest wil
 l take home an apple-blossom pink apron\, a jar of the curd they made\, an
 d a bag of fresh organic lemons to put your new skills to the test!\n\nMer
 rilee Olson is a chef and food preservationist with years of experience tr
 ansforming farm-fresh ingredients into culinary treasures. As the founder 
 of Preserve Farm Kitchens\, she has dedicated her work to celebrating seas
 onal produce and the timeless art of preservation\, bringing creativity\, 
 expertise\, and a deep love of good food to every class she teaches.
LOCATION:Gold Ridge Organic Farms
URL:https://www.exploretock.com/gold-ridge-organic-farms/event/600035/citr
 us-curd-workshop-with-merrilee-olson
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
