BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Painting Flora and Fauna in Watercolor
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T130000
UID:260211ZVH0fsN0t0KdhtkO4YZttQ
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nFridays\, March. 20- April 24\, 2026 10:00 AM – 
 1:00 PM\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 208\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nDrawi
 ng & Painting\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and older\n\n$275 – Registration Cost 
 $25 – Materials Fee $300 – Total Registration CostIn this six-week cou
 rse\, participants will learn a unique approach to watercolor\, intended t
 o alleviate the frustration that many experience when learning this beauti
 ful yet challenging medium.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nIn this six-week course\
 , participants will learn a unique approach to watercolor\, intended to al
 leviate the frustration that many experience when learning this beautiful 
 yet challenging medium. We will focus on strengthening one’s observation
 al drawing skills\, giving the artist a foundation off of which to build t
 heir paintings in a step-by-step layering process that trains the artist t
 o see value and color. Our subject matter will be flora and fauna – a sa
 mpling of plants and animals. These subjects are great for beginners and e
 xperienced artists alike\; their organic shapes make them forgiving drawin
 g subjects\, but their beauty can be a muse for life.  Instructor Hannah 
 Day is a passionate nature lover and watercolorist and will share her uniq
 ue approach to rendering botanicals and animal portraits in watercolor. Th
 is class will work both from photographs and from life\, practicing observ
 ational drawing in addition to watercolor technique. With six class sessio
 ns\, participants will have the opportunity to develop their skills and bu
 ild muscle memory with a medium that often feels like it has a mind of its
  own.  This class is open to artists of all skill levels. All materials a
 re provided.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/painting-flora-and-fauna/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sebastopol Documentary Film Festival
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T170000
UID:251229yf7AE6_dt0eSN7m85pMWdQ
DESCRIPTION:Revolutionizing the Film Festival Experience\n\nThe Sebastopol
  Documentary Film Festival is the San Francisco Bay Area's premier documen
 tary film festival\, offering four days of curated films\, award presentat
 ions\, cinephile panels and forums\, upscale gatherings\, VIP receptions\,
  and casual meet-and-greets-all in the heart of Sonoma County.\n\nFrom its
  roots as a local fest showing about 40 films in 2007\, SDFF now receives 
 more than 700 submissions from 62\\+ countries per year. In 2025\, 57 film
 s were programmed and shown and the event was attended by filmmakers\, as 
 well as a robust audience of film lovers. In addition to its commitment to
  honoring diversity in all its forms by providing open calls for entry\, S
 DFF is an Oscar®-qualifying film festival for short and mini form documen
 taries.\n\nSDFF is proudly progressive in its curation of topics and forms
 . Now more than ever\, festival organizers seek to amplify urgent messages
 \, uplift stories from marginalized communities\, and support earnest effo
 rts to provoke political change\, effect social justice\, and encourage pe
 rsonal growth\n\nFor more information about how you can submit your film\,
  volunteer to help with the fest\, donate money\, or promote our vital wor
 k\, please visit https://www.sebastopolfilm.org/.\n\nAbout SDFF \\(Sebasto
 pol Documentary Film Festival\\):\n\nFounded in 2007\, the first ever Seba
 stopol Documentary Film Festival \\(SDFF\\) boldly curated 44 films that b
 rought into focus a wealth of talented filmmakers from Sonoma County and t
 he greater San Francisco Bay Area.\n\nSixteen years later\, nearly 700 tit
 les from 62 countries were openly submitted for SDFF 2023. Sixty-three fil
 ms were programmed\, the event was attended by 93 filmmakers and an impres
 sive audience\, through in-person and streaming delivery.\n\nSDFF honors d
 iversity in all forms. We continue to provide equal opportunity for filmma
 kers through open calls for entry\; explore what it's like for any life to
  wake to its existence.\n\nSDFF is an Oscar® qualifying Film Festival for
  documentaries in the short form. Sebastopol Documentary Film Festival is 
 proudly progressive\, often featuring spotlights on social justice\, journ
 alism\, current issues. When the right films come through we've programmed
  different POV's of the same story. Given the proliferation of AI\, docume
 ntaries might become our only touchstone for what was 'real' at a moment i
 n time. What better platform than a non-fiction film festival to encourage
  fresh and critical thinking?\n\nDate and Time: Thursday\, 09 April 2026 a
 t 09:00 - Sunday\, 12 April 2026 at 17:00
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center For The Arts
URL:https://www.sebastopolfilm.org/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
