BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:INTO THE LIGHT: Light-filled aintings by Katy Boggs
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T170000
UID:260330tk93i17RL0GXbHXlmiJmHA
DESCRIPTION:Katy's paintings are an exploration of light—how it shapes f
 orm\, reveals color\, and defines what we see.\n\n"I am drawn to moments w
 here light is felt as much as seen: filtering through dense leaves\, tower
 ing in the crowns of trees\, glinting off cresting waves\, or softening in
 to the quiet glow of a sunset. Light is everywhere\; without it\, there is
  no seeing. Beyond its physical presence\, it also carries a deeper resona
 nce as a symbol of hope. In a time of uncertainty\, this work seeks to bri
 ng light into the image\, both visually and metaphorically."\n\nReception:
  April 25\, 4 to 6 pm.
LOCATION:Sebastopol Gallery
URL:http://sebastopolgallery.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Great Literacy Adventure: A Free Community Event
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T150000
UID:260330gnL1XiIwpUSSEYkLv4bUvA
DESCRIPTION:This joyous\, daylong event at NorCal Public Media brings toge
 ther families\, community partners\, and dynamic literacy advocates — fr
 om beloved PBS characters to nationally recognized authors — for a joyfu
 l\, inclusive literacy experience with more than 15 activities for childr
 en. Literacy Promise partners will be on hand to connect families with res
 ources and tips for promoting reading at home.\n\nSome of the highlights b
 eing planned include:\n\n\\*Buddy the Dinosaur and Carl the Collector from
  PBS Kids\n\n\\*Otto the Otter from the Sonoma County Library\n\n\\*Litera
 cy Quest for the Great Scholastic Book treasure chest (free books while su
 pplies last)\n\n\\*Live story times with special guest readers\n\n\\*Book 
 signings by authors including Matthew Gollub and Marissa McGee\n\n\\*“O
 n air” and “green screen” experiences in the KRCB studios make child
 ren the stars of radio- and video-style segments\n\n\\*Visit a firetruck 
 and crew from Rohnert Park Department of Public Safety Fire\n\n\\*Food ava
 ilable for purchase from local food trucks Sol Azteca\, World Famous Cornd
 ogs\, and Kona Ice\n\n\\*Engaging literacy experiences hosted by the Son
 oma County Literacy Promise partners\n\nAnd so much more!
LOCATION:Nor-Cal Public Media
URL:https://www.scoe.org/adventure
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Emergence - Spring Through the Eyes of the Artists
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T160000
UID:260326rcNM2F4mZkuHURfXDOmDzA
DESCRIPTION:"Emergence" brings together the Artists of Fulton Crossing to 
 explore what Spring means to their creative lives. Spring is more than a s
 eason. It's a metaphor. It's renewal\, risk\, color\, thawing\, blooming\,
  awakening\, and sometimes even struggles. The public is invited to enjoy 
 this free Art exhibit and to take time to wander through the artists studi
 os and gallery spaces. Meet the artists at our opening reception March 21s
 t. Upcoming Art Workshops: March 21: Painting Easter Cookies. April 18: Ci
 gar Box Collage. May 16: Succulent Garden Centerpiece. Make treasures to b
 ring home. All ages welcome. Materials provided. E-mail Brenda at nanaspre
 ttypaper@outlook.com for preregistration and workshop info.
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/emergence-spring-through-the-eyes-of-
 the-artists/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bachata Beginners Saturday
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T120000
UID:260325m3CUO9Ub8kqWr32m4o25Tw
DESCRIPTION:This class is perfect for bachata beginners that want to learn
  basic steps and skills\, or those who want to refresh their foundational 
 skills. We understand that learning something new can feel a little intimi
 dating. That’s why our supportive and relaxed environment is specificall
 y designed to make learning bachata basics an absolute blast!\n\nOur frien
 dly instructors will guide you through:\n\nBasic directional steps: You
 ’ll learn the fundamental movements that form the building blocks of all
  bachata dancing.\n\nProper frame for partner work: Discover how to conne
 ct comfortably and effectively with a partner\, setting you up for smooth 
 and enjoyable dances.\n\nSimple turn patterns: We’ll introduce you to e
 asy-to-follow turn patterns that will have you dancing with a partner in n
 o time.\n\nWe’ve carefully organized our curriculum to ensure that each 
 movement is easy to grasp and remember\, building your confidence with eve
 ry step. Our goal is to make learning fun. Join us to learn Bachata in Mar
 in.\n\nImportant Details\n\nNo dance experience required: Whether you’v
 e never danced before or it’s been a while\, you’re welcome here!\n\nN
 o partner necessary: Come solo or bring a friend—either way\, you’ll 
 have plenty of opportunities to dance.\n\nPlease wear non-marking shoe so
 les: This helps us keep our dance floor in great condition.\n\nCome join 
 us and discover the joy of bachata! We can’t wait to see you on the danc
 e floor.\n\nDate & Time:\n\nThursdays @ 6:30PM – 7:30PM Fridays @ 5:30PM
  – 6:30PM Saturdays @ 9:00 AM – 10:00 AM\n\nInstructor: Lucie Ebnerova
 \n\nAddress: 4140 Redwood Highway \\#8 San Rafael\, CA\n\nNote: Arrive 10 
 minutes before. No floor marking shoe soles allowed.
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8 San Rafael
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/bachata-beginners-satur
 day/17624456/2026-04-11T11
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
