BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:INTO THE LIGHT: Light-filled aintings by Katy Boggs
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T170000
UID:260330J2GWojoYBEmsq02dFXhpLw
DESCRIPTION:Katy's paintings are an exploration of light—how it shapes f
 orm\, reveals color\, and defines what we see.\n\n"I am drawn to moments w
 here light is felt as much as seen: filtering through dense leaves\, tower
 ing in the crowns of trees\, glinting off cresting waves\, or softening in
 to the quiet glow of a sunset. Light is everywhere\; without it\, there is
  no seeing. Beyond its physical presence\, it also carries a deeper resona
 nce as a symbol of hope. In a time of uncertainty\, this work seeks to bri
 ng light into the image\, both visually and metaphorically."\n\nReception:
  April 25\, 4 to 6 pm.
LOCATION:Sebastopol Gallery
URL:http://sebastopolgallery.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Emergence - Spring Through the Eyes of the Artists
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T160000
UID:260326A_LymtQ8VUyVlx5HvVg4ew
DESCRIPTION:"Emergence" brings together the Artists of Fulton Crossing to 
 explore what Spring means to their creative lives. Spring is more than a s
 eason. It's a metaphor. It's renewal\, risk\, color\, thawing\, blooming\,
  awakening\, and sometimes even struggles. The public is invited to enjoy 
 this free Art exhibit and to take time to wander through the artists studi
 os and gallery spaces. Meet the artists at our opening reception March 21s
 t. Upcoming Art Workshops: March 21: Painting Easter Cookies. April 18: Ci
 gar Box Collage. May 16: Succulent Garden Centerpiece. Make treasures to b
 ring home. All ages welcome. Materials provided. E-mail Brenda at nanaspre
 ttypaper@outlook.com for preregistration and workshop info.
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/emergence-spring-through-the-eyes-of-
 the-artists/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:World Dance
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T110000
UID:260324dY_W_bQ_EE-_Ir_Vefni5w
DESCRIPTION:Travel the World—No Passport Required!\n\nEvery Sunday at 10
 :00 AM\, grab your global one-way ticket to fitness. We’re traveling acr
 oss continents through rhythm and movement\, blending high-energy world da
 nces with a full-body workout. Whether you’re a seasoned pro or have two
  left feet\, come sweat\, smile\, and discover your new favorite beat.\n\n
 Who: All adult ages and skill levels.\n\nWhen: Sundays @ 10:00 AM.\n\nTh
 e Vibe: Pure fun\, global rhythms\, and a community that moves together.\
 n\nAbout Zeena\n\nZeena Quinn’s World Dance classes are based on learnin
 g coordination\, motivating the brain\, dance techniques\, and therefore\,
  mind-body transformation. By creating a supportive system\, participants 
 discover themselves in their own way via dance.\n\nParticipants will work 
 upper and lower body\, cardio and mostly rhythms & coordination. One will 
 understand and learn to identify the different rhythms while having fun! Z
 eena has a lifetime of experience in dance\, professional performance\, ch
 oreography\, teaching\, as well as\, in fitness and resistance training.\n
 \nZeena has toured the Bay Area presenting a variety of American swing\, C
 harlston\, hip hop\, disco\, line dances\, and international dance styles 
 such as Bollywood\, Afro-Brazilian/Samba\, Flamenco\, and European and Eas
 tern Folk. These authentic dance techniques demonstrate how our body is an
  instrument. Because of her extensive range of dance training\, she brings
  the authenticity of technique into her vibrant teaching style.\n\nCome ta
 ke a trip around theworld! Comfortable clothes and worn shoes that tie. No
  Hoka or hiking shoes please.
LOCATION:Salsa Dance Marin
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/world-dance/18336667/20
 26-04-12T10
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
