BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Quench at Copia: "GOAT"-ed Grapes- Cabernet Edition
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T183000
UID:260325P3hI9BgSW0egx0eMom1dHw
DESCRIPTION:CIA at Copia is proud to be the home of the newest wine tastin
 g experience and podcast series\, Quench at Copia\, with Master Sommelie
 r Andrea Immer Robinson. You will get to be part of a live studio audience
  through a guided tasting with special guests from the culinary and wine i
 ndustries who will join along the way. Each event invites you to learn an
 d connect through exceptional wines\, thoughtful pairings\, and lively con
 versation. \n\nCabernet lovers\, this one is for you. We welcome you to
  be part of CIA at Copia’s newest wine tasting experience with Master
  Sommelier Andrea Immer Robinson in her Quench at Copia series\, with 
 special guests and winemaking minds behind Heitz Cellar\, Brittany Sherwoo
 d and Master Sommelier Erik Elliot. In this experience\, you’ll be fo
 cusing on one of the “GOAT”-ed Grapes: Cabernet. Through a guide
 d tasting and expert insight\, you’ll uncover what gives Cabernet its 
 power\, elegance\, and unmistakable character.\n\nThis experience will als
 o be paired with a “Taste of The Grove” – a sample of a dish from
  The Grove Restaurant curated by our former CIA student and Michelin-st
 arred chef.
LOCATION:CIA at Copia
URL:https://www.ciaatcopia.com/quench-wine-podcast-at-copia/?utm_source=we
 bsite&utm_medium=organic&utm_campaign=quench-at-copia-city-spark
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
