BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Photographing Your Roses
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T200000
UID:260330PgHOhKM3yEy7QeS93YGTJw
DESCRIPTION:Presented by Betty Mott\, Master Rosarian. Betty will share si
 mple techniques for capturing the beauty of roses\, printing your images a
 nd framing them\, and how to best style and shoot your blooms. For those w
 anting to enter your rose pictures into the Spring Rose Show\, Betty will 
 offer valuable tips on how to present award-winning rose photography that 
 will catch a judge's eye!\n\nWhat to bring: One or two 8x10 glossy prints.
  You will be given a free photo mat\, backing and protective sleeve for ea
 ch photo. Betty will demonstrate how to mount a photo to best show off you
 r artistry.\n\nAbout Betty Mott: An active member of the Marin Rose Societ
 y and Santa Clarita Rose Society\, Betty is an ARS Horticulture Judge\, Ph
 otography Judge\, Master Rosarian and ARS Bronze Honor Medal recipient. At
  the District level\, Betty has served in a wide variety of positions incl
 uding Secretary\, Program and Speakers Chair\, member of the Bylaws Revisi
 on Committee and her current role as Photography Judges Chair.\n\n"Roses h
 ave always been a part of my life. Growing up in New England learning from
  my Dad's organic gardening practices helped grow my love for nature\, whi
 ch fueled my passion for photography. One of my great joys is photographin
 g roses outside with natural lighting to tell a story that brings you back
  again and again to gaze upon the image with wonder."--Betty Mott
LOCATION:Luther Burbank Art & Garden Center
URL:https://www.sonomaroses.org/programs
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
