BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dumpling Workshop with Lani Chan at Gold Ridge Organic Farms
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T130000
UID:260325uEeQKImB2kK3hILgn3a8YQ
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a 3-hour hands-on dumpling workshop led by Lani Ch
 an\, founder of Hei Ma\, where you'll learn to make dumplings entirely fro
 m scratch — wrappers\, fillings\, and all. You'll start by making the do
 ugh using heirloom grain flours grown by our Sebastopol neighbor Farmer Ma
 i\, who will be on hand to share the story behind their remarkable grains.
  From there\, you'll form and cook vegetarian dumplings\, learn to make sc
 allion pancakes\, and pair everything with Hei Ma chili crisp and a specia
 l dipping sauce made with Gold Ridge Organic Farms Apple Cider Balsamic Vi
 negar.\n\nThe experience begins with a ride aboard our apple-themed trolle
 y out to the Apple Cottage\, where the class will take place surrounded by
  the beauty of the farm. Each guest will receive an apple-blossom pink apr
 on to take home and enjoy a refreshing citrus shrub alongside their freshl
 y made dumplings. Whether you're a seasoned home cook or a first-time dump
 ling maker\, this is an experience you won't forget — good food\, great 
 company\, and a deeper connection to the ingredients grown right here in S
 onoma County.\n\nLani Chan is the co-founder of Hei Ma (formerly known as 
 Big Spoon Sauce Co.)\, a Sonoma County-based small-batch sauce brand roote
 d in Chinese culinary tradition and peak-season California produce. What b
 egan as a chili crisp project in a Brooklyn apartment in 2019 has grown in
 to a community-driven food brand celebrated for its bold flavors and cultu
 ral heart.\n\nMai Nguyen is an award-winning heirloom grain farmer\, mille
 r\, seed keeper\, and community organizer based right here in Sebastopol. 
 In 2024\, their work was recognized with the prestigious James Beard Leade
 rship Award for their contributions to sustainability\, equity\, and justi
 ce in food systems\, collaborating with communities and coalitions to shap
 e food policy that uplifts marginalized farmers and promotes land sovereig
 nty.
LOCATION:Gold Ridge Organic Farms
URL:https://www.exploretock.com/gold-ridge-organic-farms/event/599710/dump
 ling-workshop-with-lani-chan
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
