BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T180000
UID:260318-M2jkBPw2UKvXSSEBUYyyw
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\nAPRIL EXHIBIT: THE PO
 ETIC LANDSCAPE\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\nRECEP
 TION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILLER and
  PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by feature
 d guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.  Be 
 sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beautiful 
 work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.\n\nSonoma County 
 artist\, Karen Miller\, presents The Poetic Landscape\, pastel paintings t
 hat convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting with the intrinsic
  beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid shapes and rhyt
 hmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true poetic interlud
 e.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,” turning to the 
 sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the river’s edge\
 , concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing in “Fetch.”
   The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a shaded secret sp
 ot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\, these works tru
 ly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Miller remarked “ 
 As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surrounding us\, I try to 
 express my painterly response in hopes it will engender recognition by the
  viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting the Gallery on M
 arch 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stairway Smallworks 
 Showcase features Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\, a collection of waterco
 lors that create an atmosphere that is both introspective and magical.  F
 amiliar domestic scenes are transformed as humans interact with animals an
 d birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” the red-headed young
  woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahead\, flanked by her 
 avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like taking a mini-step o
 n the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nMeet the artist: Rapp
  will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 from 11am to 6 pm.\n
 \nAlso join us for ART NITE HEALDSBURG\, Thursday\, April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.
   The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets to Art.  ART NITE Hea
 ldsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is a community event cele
 brating art and creativity with over 20 galleries participating.  ArtNite
 Healdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Center Street\, Healdsburg\,
  CA 95448. \\(707\\) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 pm.    www.upsta
 irsart gallery.net \n\nFor further information: Contact: Beverly Bird\, Pr
 ess Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"April in Paris" - Flower Show and Plant Sale at the Graton Commun
 ity Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T160000
UID:260316Wo1kG_9QzkyXrv8c8O-4LQ
DESCRIPTION:This world in “transition” can be horrifying and at best i
 ntense\, so this Spring 2026 the Graton Community Club has chosen to look 
 back to another time and place\, “April in Paris”. We all need a littl
 e respite.\n\nWe are offering not only our signature theme-focused flower 
 arrangements and affordable spring garden plants and veggie starts\, but a
 n outing at "Café de Graton" in the dining room with a French-themed lunc
 heon\, beverages and homemade desserts\, all for $15.\n\nTake a welcome br
 eak from the intensity and join us on April 17 and 18 in downtown Graton. 
 Hours are 9am-4pm both days. You'll find one-of-a kind handmade crafts and
  novelties\, live local music and community connections. Then take that LO
 VE back into the world — we all need it. ALL are welcome\, Free admissio
 n. Proceeds from this event will go towards providing scholarships for loc
 al area students\, as well as helping maintain our historic building.
LOCATION:Graton Community Club
URL:https://gratoncommunityclub.org
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
