BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Breathing Room: Writing for Stillness and Peace
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T120000
UID:260218d__edtxFXEicEWOoVhkYXg
DESCRIPTION:Online Mini-Retreat with James Crews Breathing Room: Writing f
 or Stillness and Peace\n\nSaturday\, April 18\, 10-12 PT \\(1-3 pm ET\\)\n
 \nJoin poet and editor James Crews for a supportive and encouraging retrea
 t focusing on rest and peace through writing. We will work from poems and 
 prompts from his latest book\, Breathing Room \\(available March 17\\)\, a
 nd create together in a stress-free and tender space. \n\nThere will be t
 ime for sharing what you write\, if you wish\, but there is no pressure to
  do so\, and this workshop is ideal for writers of all levels and backgrou
 nds.\n\nJames Crews is the author of Turning Toward Grief: Reflections on 
 Life\, Loss & Appreciation\, Breathing Room: Poems of Rest & Retreat\, and
  editor of several bestselling poetry anthologies\, including Love Is for 
 All of Us\, a collection of LGBTQ\\+ love poems co-edited with his husband
 \, Brad Peacock. He has also edited The Wonder of Small Things \\(winner o
 f the New England Book Award\\)\, The Path to Kindness \\(winner of the Na
 utilus Award\\)\, and How to Love the World\, which has sold over 100\,000
  copies to date. He has been featured on NPR’s Morning Edition\, and in 
 People Magazine\, The Boston Globe\, The New York Times Magazine\, The Sun
  Magazine\, and The Washington Post. James lives with his husband on forty
  rocky acres in Vermont that they are restoring to a habitat for pollinato
 rs and native species. jamescrews.net\n\nRegister at http://stcolumbasinve
 rness.org/breathing-room
LOCATION:St. Columba's Inverness
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/breathing-room-writing-
 for-stillness-and-peace/18150260/2026-04-18T10
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Patterns + Printing for Kids
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T120000
UID:2602149LJYuqGtj0G8T-JJT-AEeg
DESCRIPTION:From Stamp to Table: Picnic Pattern Workshop\n\nStep into the 
 world of design and pattern-making! In this hands-on workshop\, kids will 
 explore the art of repeating patterns — just like real textile designers
 . Using hand-carved stamps\, rollers\, and stencils\, each participant wil
 l create their own bold\, colorful designs and print them on cotton tablec
 loths or picnic napkin sets to take home.\n\nWe’ll talk about color\, ba
 lance\, and rhythm in design — then bring those ideas to life on fabric.
  The result? A totally functional\, one-of-a-kind textile piece perfect fo
 r family picnics\, kitchen tables\, or gifting.
LOCATION:Art Escape
URL:https://artescapesonoma.jumbula.com/Spring2026/PatternsPrintingforKids
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Butter & Egg Days Parade & Festival 2026
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T170000
UID:260212nGb8uSvu7kCUKxBVtAPFCQ
DESCRIPTION:Theme: "America's Birthday - Petaluma Style"\n\nCelebrating 2
 50 years of independence\, ingenuity\, and small-town pride.\n\n“America
 s’ Birthday – Petaluma Style” celebrates the nation’s 250th Birthd
 ay by honoring Petaluma’s deep agricultural roots and hometown spirit. T
 his year’s Butter & Egg Days Parade recognizes the farmers\, families\, 
 immigrants\, makers\, entrepreneurs\, and creatives whose hard work\, imag
 ination\, and ingenuity reflect the enduring American Dream. This celebrat
 ion also pays respect to the Indigenous peoples who first stewarded this l
 and\, the courage of our founders\, and the dedication of the dairy and eg
 g farming community that shaped our town. Rooted in community\, innovation
 \, and independence\, the parade celebrates the small-town spirit that con
 tinues to make Petaluma a vibrant place to call home. Head to Downtown Pet
 aluma and celebrate with our community on this day of fun\, history\, and 
 local pride!\n\nParade participants incorporate the theme “America's Bi
 rthday - Petaluma Style” into their entry design. The theme gives nonpr
 ofits\, businesses\, organizations\, and individuals lots of options for s
 howing off their creativity in their designs. All parade entries will be j
 udged on how well their entry portrays this year's theme - winners announc
 ed on the website! Check back later to see which entries take home the pri
 zes and earn bragging rights.\n\nThe Butter & Egg Days festivities kick of
 f on Saturday\, April 11 with the Opening Ceremonies at the Petaluma Hi
 storical Library and Museum \\(20 Fourth St\\)\, from Noon to 1pm. Mayor K
 evin McDonnell will read a proclamation honoring the Grand Marshal and Goo
 d Egg. Come enjoy this display that shows the heart of our community.\n\nO
 ne week later on Saturday\, April 18\, the Butter & Egg Days Parade ste
 ps off at noon and marches through the historic downtown. The parade showc
 ases over 100 units with approximately 3\,000 participants and 200 volunte
 ers. Clover Sonoma returns to lead the Clover Kids’ Parade\, which prec
 edes the main parade at 11:30am with a procession of preschoolers and prim
 ary grade youngsters and their families.\n\nThe parade is surrounded by a
  Festival that spreads over four city blocks from 10am-5pm offering a wid
 e variety of food\, crafts\, beverage gardens\, two large kid areas\, live
  music\, and more! This annual event aims to bring together the community 
 for a day of fun and entertainment.\n\nThe following weekend\, Downtown Pe
 taluma continues the celebration with the Annual Spring Antique Faire\, on
  Sunday\, April 26.\n\nHappy Butter & Egg Days!!!\n\nVisit ButterAndEggDa
 ys.com for more information!
LOCATION:Historic Downtown Petaluma
URL:http://www.ButterAndEggDays.com 
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
