BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:American Red Cross Adult and Pediatric First-Aid/CPR/AED Class (Bl
 ended)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T134500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T161500
UID:260325_ARET4hWVUqyQW2hNHJhRQ
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to save a life!\n\nFocusing on recognizing and treat
 ing adults\, children and babies experiencing life-threatening situations 
 in the critical minutes before 911 arrives\, we will cover how to handle c
 hoking\, cardiac arrest\, severe bleeding\, sudden illness\, heart attack\
 , stroke - and more. We'll make sure everyone leaves the class prepared to
  step in and provide help.\n\nThis is a blended class offering the best of
  both worlds: Watch the presentations and related material online at your 
 convenience before heading to the in-person session to practice our skills
  in a small-group setting\, with our friendly and patient instructor answe
 ring questions along the way. Your American Red Cross certificate will be 
 valid for 2 years.\n\n(This community class event is held at a branch of S
 onoma County Library. We thank them for their hospitality. They have reque
 sted that we mention that this program is neither sponsored by nor affilia
 ted with the Sonoma County Library. Done!)\n\nPlease check out our website
  for more details\, and feel free to get in touch with any questions. Hope
  to see you there!
LOCATION:Petaluma Regional Library
URL:https://riverpreparedfirstaid.com/community-classes/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
