DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T163000
UID:26032688fB9ifoG0Gl66fV6WcrfA
DESCRIPTION:Processing and moving through grief with the earth as our guid
 ing force. This weekly community circle is a time to connect with yourself
  and the earth by physically moving and engaging with the earth\, sun\, ai
 r\, and water to help release. Sometimes talk therapy is not enough and we
  need to find other ways of working through our sorrow. Sample Class Forma
 t Class will begin indoors with a community circle and a guided creative e
 xcersise infused with mindfulness. Then we will head out to the Land of th
 e Good garden\, surrounded by beautiful meadow views and fresh air. Togeth
 er we will embark on physical work such as: tilling soil\, propagating see
 ds\, digging beds\, planting\, weeding\, and more. What To Bring Gloves Su
 n Hat Water Bottle Snack \\(if needed\\) Sun Screen/Sun Protection
LOCATION:Santa Rosa Junior College
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/gardening-through-grief/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
