BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sonoma County Philharmonic in concert - FANNY\, FLORENCE & SAM
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T160000
UID:260330tEhr6xLQ10-_0v-069l02g
DESCRIPTION:**Norman Gamboa**\, conductor\n\n**Esther Rayo**\, soprano\n\n
 **SAMUEL COLERIDGE-TAYLOR** Idyll\, Op.44 \n\n**FANNY MENDELSSOHN** Hero 
 und Leander\n\n**FLORENCE PRICE** Symphony No. 1  \n\n**Join us for a pr
 ogram featuring three under- appreciated composers whose works are finally
  receiving the attention they deserve.**\n\n ♪ **Samuel Coleridge-Tayl
 or’s lovely *Idyll*** sets a reflective and poetic tone with its tender
  melodies and pastoral elegance.\n\n♪ **Fanny Mendelssohn’s dramatic 
 cantata\, *Hero und Leander***\, weaves a tragic Greek myth into music of
  passion and vivid orchestration.\n\n♪ **Florence Price’s groundbreak
 ing *Symphony No. 1*** blends classical forms with African American spir
 ituals and folk rhythms creating an iconic 20th century American masterpie
 ce. \n\n​**Come celebrate the breadth of orchestral music and its endur
 ing power to surprise\, delight\, and move the human spirit!**
LOCATION:Jackson Theater\, Sonoma Country Day School
URL:https://www.socophil.org/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:INTO THE LIGHT: Light-filled aintings by Katy Boggs
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T170000
UID:2603309YZMRMKj6UqLJBwNKmmuGw
DESCRIPTION:Katy's paintings are an exploration of light—how it shapes f
 orm\, reveals color\, and defines what we see.\n\n"I am drawn to moments w
 here light is felt as much as seen: filtering through dense leaves\, tower
 ing in the crowns of trees\, glinting off cresting waves\, or softening in
 to the quiet glow of a sunset. Light is everywhere\; without it\, there is
  no seeing. Beyond its physical presence\, it also carries a deeper resona
 nce as a symbol of hope. In a time of uncertainty\, this work seeks to bri
 ng light into the image\, both visually and metaphorically."\n\nReception:
  April 25\, 4 to 6 pm.
LOCATION:Sebastopol Gallery
URL:http://sebastopolgallery.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Seaweed Foraging on the Sonoma Coast
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T063000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T090000
UID:260328tXvGgMicEUiEbwtbQvFN2g
DESCRIPTION:This 2.5 hour guided morning foray will meet on the Sonoma Coa
 st\, and be followed by a talk on what you collected\, the ecology of seaw
 eed\, and how to cook your harvest. You can expect to collect up to 10 lbs
 . of raw edible seaweed. This is a coastal forage during low tide. You won
 't need to get in the ocean\, but we recommend wearing rain boots. Please 
 note this event is for ages 9 and up. An educational hands-on workshop · 
  Learn a new food skill ·  Explore the normally-underwater inter tidal 
 zone at a negative low tide ·  Connect with your local food system ·  
 Enjoy nutritional-rich umami direct from the source. see 'Low Tide Lessons
 ' article from Only In California
LOCATION:Sonoma Coast\, near Bodega Bay
URL:https://www.foragesf.com/seaweed-foraging-sonoma
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
