DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSession 1: Tuesdays\, March 31 – April 21\, 2026
  6:00 PM – 9:00 PM Session 2: Tuesdays\, April 28 – May 19\, 2026 6:00
  PM – 9:00 PM\n\nExperience Level\n\nIntermediate\n\nCeramics\n\nAge\\(s
 \\)\n\n17\\+\n\nSingle Session – 4 weeks: $140 Registration Fee $30 Mate
 rials Fee $170 Total Registration Fee\n\nBoth Sessions – 8 weeks: $265 R
 egistration Fee $30 Materials Fee $295 Total Registration FeeWork independ
 ently on personal projects with the direct support of an instructor by you
 r side in this Independent Projects Class with Amy Hamley.\n\nWhat you’l
 l do\n\nThis session has been split into 2\, 4 week sessions – you can 
 enroll in each session independently or enroll in both as a package deal!T
 his course is for students interested in exploring both wheel throwing AND
  handbuilding\, and the combination of both in one class! Learn from Hamle
 y’s years of expertise in the field and enjoy creating handbuilt\, throw
 n\, and altered forms. Amy caters each syllabus closely to her group of st
 udents\, ensuring that every project fits the desires of participants. Thi
 s course encourages folks to work on independent projects in the class\, r
 eceiving one on one support from Amy throughout the time. This course will
  include demos\, exercises\, and utilize a variety of methods to achieve t
 he desired goal for each student. Some projects may include wheel thrown v
 ases with altered adornments\, best practices for slump and hump molds\, a
 nd more.\n\nMembership has its benefits\n\nAll Silver Memberships and abov
 e receive 10% off the registration cost for any class purchase over $40. M
 aterials fees are not discounted.\n\nBecome a member today and find commun
 ity\, connection\, and creativity.\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 117\, Ceramics Stud
 io
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/independent-projects/2026-0
 3-31/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
