 egories: Drawing & Painting\, Extended Classes\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and old
 er\n\nRegistration Cost:\n\n$175\n\nMaterials Fee:\n\nSee Required List\n\
 nTotal Registration Cost:\n\n$175\n\nExpress joy through drawing. Build sk
 ills in sketching\, composition & landscapes. Boost focus\, creativity\, c
 onnection & well-being.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nWhen we feel a sense of joy\
 , it is natural to express that feeling from our body. We may use our voic
 e and sing\, we may dance\, and we may use our hands in creative expressio
 n. By drawing we leave a mark of that expression. This course is shaped wi
 th skill building exercises to improve eye-hand coordination with quick sk
 etching and gesture drawing and practices of learning to see how to abstra
 ct shapes of light and dark for developing strong compositions. We will fo
 cus on landscape imagery from photos and drawing from setups in the studio
 . Drawing outside of class will be encouraged but not required. There are 
 many health benefits from drawing such as: improvements in cognitive focus
 \, freedom of expression with your hands\, the satisfaction that comes fro
 m seeing the world in a different way\, the social camaraderie of acceptan
 ce in the studio\, and the joy of doing something with your hands.\n\nRequ
 ired Materials List\n\nA good size sketch book for multimedia\n\nNewsprint
  drawing pad \\(12” x 18” or 18” x 24”\\)\n\nBlack pencils\, 6B so
 ft\n\nCompressed charcoal sticks\, black and white\n\nEraser\, kneaded rub
 ber\n\nEraser\, white vinyl\n\nBlack felt pens
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/drawing-in-joy/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T180000
UID:2603183xwo7N4yx02pvyNEGgc04A
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\nAPRIL EXHIBIT: THE PO
 ETIC LANDSCAPE\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\nRECEP
 TION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILLER and
  PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by feature
 d guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.  Be 
 sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beautiful 
 work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.\n\nSonoma County 
 artist\, Karen Miller\, presents The Poetic Landscape\, pastel paintings t
 hat convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting with the intrinsic
  beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid shapes and rhyt
 hmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true poetic interlud
 e.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,” turning to the 
 sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the river’s edge\
 , concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing in “Fetch.”
   The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a shaded secret sp
 ot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\, these works tru
 ly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Miller remarked “ 
 As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surrounding us\, I try to 
 express my painterly response in hopes it will engender recognition by the
  viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting the Gallery on M
 arch 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stairway Smallworks 
 Showcase features Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\, a collection of waterco
 lors that create an atmosphere that is both introspective and magical.  F
 amiliar domestic scenes are transformed as humans interact with animals an
 d birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” the red-headed young
  woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahead\, flanked by her 
 avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like taking a mini-step o
 n the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nMeet the artist: Rapp
  will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 from 11am to 6 pm.\n
 \nAlso join us for ART NITE HEALDSBURG\, Thursday\, April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.
   The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets to Art.  ART NITE Hea
 ldsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is a community event cele
 brating art and creativity with over 20 galleries participating.  ArtNite
 Healdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Center Street\, Healdsburg\,
  CA 95448. \\(707\\) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 pm.    www.upsta
 irsart gallery.net \n\nFor further information: Contact: Beverly Bird\, Pr
 ess Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Samba no Pé - First Class
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T193000
UID:260317FcHWScVGO0GyKvXyu8512w
DESCRIPTION:Get ready to feel the rhythm and energy of Rio de Janeiro! Sa
 mba no Pé \\(Samba in the Foot\\) is the captivating solo style of samba
  danced in the streets and at Carnival\, known for its rapid\, intricate f
 ootwork and infectious hip movements.\n\nYou will learn\n\nThe Basic Step:
  You will master the signature quick-quick-slow rhythm that defines Samba 
 no Pé.\n\nArm & Hip Styling: You will learn how to add the authentic flai
 r\, movement\, and energy that makes Brazilian samba so captivating.\n\nTe
 chnique & Posture: You will receive tips on proper body alignment to help 
 you dance longer\, faster\, and more safely.\n\nRhythm & Musicality: You w
 ill learn how to connect your movement directly to the irresistible beat o
 f the bateria \\(the samba drum section\\).\n\nThis class is perfect for a
 nyone looking to connect with the vibrant spirit of Brazil\, improve coord
 ination\, and get a fantastic workout—all while learning the foundationa
 l steps of this iconic dance. No partner or prior dance experience is requ
 ired! Just bring your enthusiasm and comfortable shoes!\n\nDate & Time: Th
 ursdays @6:30PM – 7:30PM\n\nAddress: 4140 Redwood Highway \\#8 San Rafae
 l\, CA\n\nNote: Arrive 10 minutes before. No floor marking shoe soles allo
 wed.
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8 • San Rafael
URL:https://salsadancemarin.com/samba-no-pe
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
