BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:New Moon On Monday
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T000000
UID:260327zSCUK4ufSUOYDS73pyheBQ
DESCRIPTION:New Moon on Monday is the top Duran Duran tribute band in Nort
 h America\, bringing over a decade of international touring and countless 
 sold-out shows to stages everywhere. Performing together since 2010\, the 
 group delivers a high-energy\, hit-filled concert packed with the glamour\
 , musicianship\, and showmanship that defined Duran Duran’s legacy. Thei
 r resume includes major theaters\, celebrated clubs\, and large festival a
 udiences across the U.S. and abroad.\n\nA proven draw for festivals\, casi
 nos\, theaters\, and special events\, New Moon on Monday continues to be t
 he premier choice for fans of 80s new wave and modern pop-rock spectacle.
LOCATION:Mystic Theatre & Music Hall
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/108089706?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bella Rayne Band
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T000000
UID:260327pTwYPUCxoEuhdbNTCHvdxg
DESCRIPTION:MEET BELLA RAYNE | GUITARIST\n\n18 year old Bella Rayne is a s
 elf-taught guitarist\, vocalist\, and songwriter\, born in the mountains o
 f North Carolina and raised in coastal Mendocino\, California\, whose bold
  blend of jam band energy\, Southern-tinged rock\, ’90s grunge grit\, an
 d psychedelic spirit is rapidly capturing attention across the U.S. \n\nHe
 r journey began during the pandemic\, when boredom led her to resurrect an
  old Stratocaster she found in her garage. She fixed it up\, learned to pl
 ay by ear\, and quickly found her voice — melding influences from rock\,
  Americana\, bluegrass\, and the jam-band legacy into something deeply her
  own.                                              \n\nDespite her young a
 ge\, Bella has already shared the stage with seasoned artists and respecte
 d bands. Appearances alongside Allman Betts Family Revival\, Melvin Seals 
 & JGB\, ALO\, Jackie Greene\, Oteil Burbridge\, and members of Terrapin Fa
 mily have all added to her early résumé PLUS she was touted as “one to
  watch” by her idol\, Susan Tedeschi in Guitar World Magazine.\n\nOne of
  the most iconic moments of her rising career: she was entrusted to play t
 he legendary guitar known as “Alligator” — once wielded by Jerry Gar
 cia. That honor\, courtesy of Grateful Guitars Foundation\, has become a d
 efining chapter in Bella’s journey. \n\nBella has formed her own project
 \, Bella Rayne Band — a high-energy\, guitar-driven ensemble featuring a
  young lineup of seasoned musicians. Their sets are a blend of soulful Sou
 thern-rock\, modern Americana and Grateful Dead reinterpretations plus the
 ir own originals\, earning increasing demand across venues and festivals.
LOCATION:HopMonk Tavern
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/1037895786?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=2
 87&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
