DESCRIPTION:Santa Rosa Junior College Lifelong Learning Offers a FREE cour
 se Drawing and Composition Course LL501\, Section Number  4235 \\(just sho
 w up and I will enroll you\\) Fridays 9:30 to 12:30 January 16 through May
  22 Roseland Campus: 950 S. Wright Road\, Santa Rosa CA 95407 Heritage Hal
 l Room 123 Amanda Rose Hopkins\,  ahopkins@santarosa.edu Class focuses on 
 Drawing with a focus on abstraction and Modernism using pencil\, ink\, oil
  pastel\, chalk pastel\, charcoal\, and collage with a focus on elements o
 f composition and design. We will explore various elements of design and c
 omposition in a nonjudgemental warm community atmosphere. A delightful mix
 ture of freedom and technique. SRJC offers noncredit courses for seniors a
 s part of its goal to provide lifelong learning. For information on joinin
 g a class please visit: https://lifelong.santarosa.edu/ No age limit for S
 RJC Lifelong Learning courses\, though they are tailored for seniors. Stud
 ents may register at any time during the semester. No fee for SRJC Lifelon
 g Learning courses. Contact Instructor for enrollment details\,  ahopkins@
 santarosa.edu The Sonoma County Junior College District does not discrimin
 ate on the basis of race\, religious creed\, color\, national origin\, anc
 estry\, ethnic group identification\, physical disability\, mental disabil
 ity\, medical condition\, genetic condition\, marital status\, sex\, gende
 r\, gender identity\, gender expression\, genetic information or sexual or
 ientation in any of its policies\, procedures or practices\; nor does the 
 District discriminate against any employees or applicants for employment o
 n the basis of their age. This non-discrimination policy covers admission\
 , access and treatment in District programs and activities--including but 
 not limited to academic admissions\, financial aid\, educational services 
 and athletics--and application for District employment. This class focuses
  on Drawing with a focus on abstraction and Modernism using pencil\, ink\,
  oil pastel\, chalk pastel\, charcoal\, and collage with a focus on elemen
 ts of composition and design. We will explore various elements of design a
 nd composition in a nonjudgemental warm community atmosphere. A delightful
  mixture of freedom and technique. Each week we will explore a different d
 rawing material and practice making various types of marks with it. We wil
 l also view drawing works by well known and obscure artists from the past 
 and present. Drawing and Composition will explore the fundamentals of comp
 osition and design in drawing and View more
