DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T000000
UID:260327MQAzR-3PWEKOpnFMDcBm1Q
DESCRIPTION:Callie Watts is a singer/songwriter from Northern California w
 ho was raised on classical music\, The Beatles and The Beach Boys before d
 iscovering Joni Mitchell\, Elton John\, Stevie Wonder\, Paul Simon\, Billy
  Joel\, Carole King\, and all the great writers of the ’60s and 70’s w
 ho have influenced her sound and writing style. After graduating high scho
 ol\, Callie began playing and performing solo\, as well as in local and ba
 y area bands of different genres. She’s played blues with Eric Lindell a
 nd the Reds\, funky soul with Phatty\, and jazz/swing with Savoy Swingers 
 along with many other various projects. Callie has taken turns throughout 
 her career as a keyboardist\, guitarist\, writer\, and lead/backing vocali
 st\, and she’s currently a member of the dynamic Sonoma County funk rock
  band Burrows and Dilbeck\, having joined in 2010 as part of the former ba
 nd Frobeck. Over time\, she’s had the honor of opening for acts such as 
 Bootsy Collins\, Elvin Bishop\, Huey Lewis and The News\, War\, Ozomatli\,
  Bill Champlin\, Booker T\, and the B52s. Callie continues to perform freq
 uently as an acoustic solo artist\, focusing on developing a core audience
  and a buzz for her original material. Come hang out and listen at venues 
 such as Aroma Roasters\, Rincon Valley Tap Room and Bottle Shop\, and Hopm
 onk Tavern.
LOCATION:HopMonk Tavern
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/108014161?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:West Marin Impressions  Natural Egg Dyeing Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T153000
UID:2603279bz95538XEuBcDQJROocKw
DESCRIPTION:Venture to West Main to step into the country to experiment wi
 th eggs\, natural dyes and sketch some of the enchanting views found at B
 lack Mountain Ranch. Together we will explore and turn everyday items into
  creative expressions.\n\nConnect the Dots Art Studio is bringing an ag-a
 nd eco-based inquiry-driven\, hands-on egg dying workshop to Black Mounta
 in Ranch—and you are invited to get creative with the artists/educators 
 from Connect the Dots who specialize in making art experiences engaging\, 
 accessible\, and unforgettable. Using Natural Egg Dye you will use plants
  to stencil designs onto eggs. Red cabbage and yellow onions will turn
  into robin egg-blue and toasty cinnamon colors that are sure to please th
 e palette. You’ll be directed on how to draw some West Marin plants and
  turn your creations into labels for the jam jars for you to transport you
 r goods home safely.\n\nBlack Mountain Ranch and its expert ranch hands w
 ill take you on a guided hike that includes breath-taking views of West 
 Marin and a visit to the pond. You’ll explore the barnyard to see the sh
 eep and alpacas. The three-story barn doubles as an event space and incl
 udes a must-see Wool Studio. A light charcuterie board will please the s
 enses and keep the energy going strong throughout the afternoon.\n\nAll pa
 rticipants will make art—they’ll observe\, question\, experiment\, and
  connect creativity to eco and ag-based awareness and creations. Expect cu
 riosity\, collaboration\, and plenty of “whoa\, that worked?!” moments
 .\n\nDon’t miss out\; sign up soon because spots are limited and expecte
 d to fill fast! Your ticket includes all the necessary supplies. Sorry\, n
 o refunds. Please wear comfortable walking shoes. Enjoy plenty of free par
 king. No pets\, it’s a working ranch.\n\nBy the end of the afternoon\, e
 veryone will take home their own egg-cellent creations—and you’ll be i
 nvited to share your creations online using \\#connectthedotsartstudo an
 d \\#blackmountainranch.
LOCATION:Black Mountain Ranch
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/west-marin-impressions-
 natural-egg-dyeing-workshop/18414195/2026-04-25T13
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
