SUMMARY:Throwing Skills Workshop with Visiting Artist Amy Palatnick
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T160000
UID:260324mE9LzdeyZEWAvDHjXi6fgQ
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSaturday\, April 25\, 2026 10:00 AM – 4:00 PM\n\
 nLocation\n\nRoom 117\, Ceramics Studio\n\nExperience Level\n\nIntermediat
 e and Advanced\n\nEvent Categories: Ceramics\, Workshops\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n
 17\\+\n\n$165 – Registration Cost \\(Includes Clay\\)\n\nLearn essential
  body care practices and master the Claw Pull technique in this immersive 
 one-day pottery workshop with full-time Studio Potter Amy Palatnick.\n\nAb
 out the Class\n\nJoin full time Studio Potter Amy Palatnick for an immersi
 ve one-day workshop designed to support your body in the studio and streng
 then your foundational wheelthrowing technique. Body and Self-Care in the 
 Studio: Start the day by learning essential practices for sustaining a lon
 g\, healthy\, and joyful pottery life. Amy will guide you through practica
 l body-care strategies that promote alignment\, ease\, and comfort as you 
 work—helping you prevent strain\, reduce soreness\, and feel more comfor
 table as you work. The Claw Pull Technique\; In the afternoon\, you’ll d
 ive into Amy’s signature Claw Pull—the foundational technique first pu
 ll that moves a lot of clay and sets you up for strong\, even-walled cylin
 ders. Through demonstration\, guided practice\, and personalized feedback\
 , you’ll begin building the muscle memory and confidence to integrate th
 is transformative technique into your throwing.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/throwing-skills-workshop/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
