BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Inspire Napa Valley Event Support Alzheimer's and Dementia Researc
 h
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T100000
UID:260309YB6gsySnvkOCZDTuy4q1jw
DESCRIPTION:The seventh annual Inspire Napa Valley will take place from Fr
 iday\, April 24 – Sunday\, April 26 in Napa Valley. Hosted by Kerrin L
 az\, founder of K. LAZ WINE COLLECTION\, the wine community and beyond to
  raise funds and awareness to advance Alzheimer’s and dementia research
  nationally and enhance local care and support services for impacted fami
 lies. Since its inception in 2017\, the event has raised over $9 milli
 on for these vital efforts. This impactful event continues to unite win
 e industry leaders and enthusiasts to raise awareness\, spark change\, a
 nd secure national funding for an incredible cause. Don't miss out on 
 this inspiring weekend that combines the best of Napa Valley with a commi
 tment to making a difference!Events include:\n\nFriday\, April 24 | VIP We
 lcome Dinner – The Best of Oakville\n\n5:30 PM | Gamble Estates\, Oakvil
 le\, CA\n\nAn exclusive evening\, The Best of Oakville\, brings together e
 ight of the region’s best wineries as co-hosts\, sharing their stories a
 nd wines\, from rare library selections to current releases. The experienc
 e is paired with a wine country feast led by Napa Valley’s own Chef Sean
  Massey and joined in the kitchen by some of wine country’s leading vint
 ners\, winemakers\, growers\, and industry icons. This intimate gathering 
 captures the spirit of true wine country hospitality.\n\nThe wineries incl
 ude Dalla Valle Vineyards\, Gamble Estates\, Harlan Estate\, Opus On\, Scr
 eaming Eagle\, Tench Vineyards\, VHR – Vine Hill Ranch\, FUTO\n\nSaturda
 y\, April 25 | VIP Alzheimer’s Research Update & Wine Tasting Seminar: D
 eep Dive Into Oakville’s Best\n\n10 AM | The Culinary Institute of Ameri
 ca at Greystone\, St. Helena\, CA\n\nFollowing an Alzheimer’s and dement
 ia research update from Inspire Napa Valley’s Scientific Advisors\, incl
 uding Gates Ventures’ Senior Director of Health & Life Sciences\, Farhad
  Imam\, guests will enjoy an in-depth exploration of six of Oakville’s m
 ost exceptional wines\, led by a distinguished panel including Antonio Gal
 loni\, founder of Vinous\, and Ray Isle\, Executive Wine Editor of Food & 
 Wine.\n\nIncluded for VIP guests. A limited number of seats are available 
 for main event guests.\n\nSaturday\, April 25 | Grand Wine Tasting\, Recep
 tion\, Dinner & Auction\n\n5 PM | Louis Martini Winery\, St. Helena\, CA\n
 \nEnjoy the walk-around Grand Tasting featuring more than 35 of California
 ’s most iconic wineries\, alongside a selection of exciting rising star 
 producers\, followed by a festive wine country dinner and Inspire Napa Val
 ley’s signature live auction and paddle raise.\n\nSunday\, April 26 | VI
 P Farewell Brunch\n\n10 AM | Ad Hoc \\+ Addendum Garden\n\nA farewell brun
 ch featuring Chef Thomas Keller’s Ad Hoc fried chicken and waffles\, alo
 ngside Bouchon seasonal dishes and a classic bloody mary and mimosa bar.
LOCATION:Louis Martini Winery
URL:https://www.inspirenapavalley.org/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
