BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mike Z at Adobe Road Winery
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T190000
UID:260331nySTKHZJDEeQVZX0dcROWQ
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a special Saturday acoustic live music set at Adob
 e Road Winery in **Downtown Petaluma**. Sip on award-winning wines while 
 enjoying talented local musicians in a warm and inviting atmosphere. Choos
 e from wines by the glass or bottle to discover new favorites. Reserve you
 r spot on **Tock** and make it a memorable night of great music\, fine w
 ine\, and good company!\n\nBorn and raised in San Francisco\, Mike Z joine
 d his first “working” band in high school. Although he started as a tr
 umpet player (which he gave up because he couldn’t talk\, let alone sing
 \, while playing)\, he switched to bass\, and then guitar. Playing in Bay 
 Area bands early in his career\, he had the opportunity to back such acts 
 as The Whispers\, The Pointer Sisters\, and Johnny Taylor.\n\nMike Z has w
 ritten original tunes for film and TV libraries\, and performed on numerou
 s studio tracks.\n\nMike Z appears currently in the bands Z and The Bender
 s and the Mike Z Jazz Trio.
LOCATION:Adobe Road Winery
URL:https://adoberoadwines.com/events/live-music-mike-z-april-25-2026/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:INTO THE LIGHT: Light-filled aintings by Katy Boggs
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T170000
UID:260330F33k3h-3r0iGVW6FzFOoPw
DESCRIPTION:Katy's paintings are an exploration of light—how it shapes f
 orm\, reveals color\, and defines what we see.\n\n"I am drawn to moments w
 here light is felt as much as seen: filtering through dense leaves\, tower
 ing in the crowns of trees\, glinting off cresting waves\, or softening in
 to the quiet glow of a sunset. Light is everywhere\; without it\, there is
  no seeing. Beyond its physical presence\, it also carries a deeper resona
 nce as a symbol of hope. In a time of uncertainty\, this work seeks to bri
 ng light into the image\, both visually and metaphorically."\n\nReception:
  April 25\, 4 to 6 pm.
LOCATION:Sebastopol Gallery
URL:http://sebastopolgallery.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
